<font color="#FF0000">FIRST MEMORIES</font><br>
<tt>Fri Sep 12 18:44:12 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I'm 30 years old and have been deeply effected by the vietnam war. I am constantly obsorbing information about the period in hopes of someday understanding what went on over there. My earliest memory of the war was on the evening news so many years ago. They spoke of &quot;guerillas&quot;, and I can still see an image of soldiers dodging in and out of the jungle along a country road. My first nightmares were of actual guerillas invading my home town. Years later I made the connection between newscast and dream. Later in college I met a vietamese-american who told me the story of escaping from his homeland and making his way to thailand were an american airline provided free travel to the U.S.. He discribed the airline food as the best meal he had ever had. Secretly I cried, feeling pain for so many people who had endured the war.
